---
import DemoLayout from '@/layouts/DemoLayout.astro'
---

<DemoLayout
  title="WebMCP Kit Developers"
  description="Developer onboarding for adding WebMCP tools to an app"
>
  <section class="developers-shell">
    <header class="developers-header">
      <p>Developer start</p>
      <h1>Add one safe app action first.</h1>
      <span>
        Start with a narrow tool, give it a strict input schema, then verify it from tests or
        devtools before adding planner complexity.
      </span>
    </header>

    <section class="developer-steps" aria-label="Developer onboarding steps">
      <article>
        <span>01</span>
        <h2>Register one tool</h2>
        <p>Expose one action the current page already owns.</p>
        <pre><code>import { defineTool, registerTool } from 'webmcp-kit'

registerTool(
  defineTool({
    name: 'select_items',
    description: 'Select visible inventory rows by stable item IDs.',
    inputSchema: {
      type: 'object',
      properties: {
        ids: {
          type: 'array',
          items: { type: 'string' }
        }
      },
      required: ['ids'],
      additionalProperties: false
    },
    execute(input) {
      return selectRows(input.ids)
    }
  })
)</code></pre>
      </article>

      <article>
        <span>02</span>
        <h2>Protect mutations</h2>
        <p>Use confirmation and guards for anything that changes important state.</p>
        <pre><code>defineTool({
  name: 'update_selected_invoice_status',
  description: 'Update the status for selected invoice rows.',
  inputSchema: {
    type: 'object',
    properties: {
      status: {
        type: 'string',
        enum: ['draft', 'sent', 'overdue', 'paid', 'void']
      }
    },
    required: ['status'],
    additionalProperties: false
  },
  confirmation: {
    required: true,
    reason: 'Changing invoice status mutates business records.'
  },
  guard() {
    return selectedInvoices.length > 0 || 'No invoices are selected.'
  },
  execute(input) {
    return updateSelectedInvoices(input.status)
  }
})</code></pre>
      </article>

      <article>
        <span>03</span>
        <h2>Call the server for secrets</h2>
        <p>Keep private APIs, payments, email, and database writes behind an app endpoint.</p>
        <pre><code>import { defineServerTool, registerTool } from 'webmcp-kit'

registerTool(
  defineServerTool({
    name: 'send_invoice',
    description: 'Send an invoice email from the server.',
    endpoint: '/api/tools/send-invoice',
    inputSchema: {
      type: 'object',
      properties: {
        invoiceId: { type: 'string' }
      },
      required: ['invoiceId'],
      additionalProperties: false
    },
    confirmation: {
      required: true,
      reason: 'Sending an invoice emails a customer.'
    }
  })
)</code></pre>
      </article>

      <article>
        <span>04</span>
        <h2>Upgrade an existing form</h2>
        <p>Turn a visible form into a tool without rebuilding the workflow.</p>
        <pre><code>import { registerFormTool } from 'webmcp-kit'

const form = document.querySelector('form')

if (form) {
  registerFormTool({
    form,
    name: 'create_support_ticket',
    description: 'Create a support ticket from the visible form.'
  })
}</code></pre>
      </article>

      <article>
        <span>05</span>
        <h2>Verify from Playwright</h2>
        <p>Inspect the registered surface and invoke tools through the app boundary.</p>
        <pre><code>import {
  invokeWebMCPTool,
  waitForWebMCPTool
} from 'webmcp-kit/testing/playwright'

await waitForWebMCPTool(page, 'select_items')

await invokeWebMCPTool(page, {
  toolName: 'select_items',
  input: { ids: ['item_4', 'item_7'] },
  source: 'planner'
})</code></pre>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="developer-checklist" aria-label="Integration checklist">
      <div>
        <span>Before adding AI</span>
        <strong>Make the tool contract boringly clear.</strong>
      </div>
      <ul>
        <li>Tool name is stable and specific.</li>
        <li>Schema is an object with required fields and no extra properties.</li>
        <li>IDs come from current page context, not model guesses.</li>
        <li>Mutating actions require confirmation.</li>
        <li>Guards reject unavailable records or impossible quantities.</li>
        <li>Tests cover the success path and at least one blocked path.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </section>
</DemoLayout>

<style>
  .developers-shell {
    display: grid;
    gap: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.5rem);
    width: min(73.75rem, calc(100% - clamp(1.25rem, 4vw, 2rem)));
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: clamp(1rem, 3vw, 1.5rem) 0 clamp(3rem, 8vw, 5rem);
  }

  .developers-header {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.65rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--demo-blue);
    padding-bottom: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.4rem);
  }

  .developers-header p,
  .developers-header h1,
  .developers-header span,
  .developer-steps h2,
  .developer-steps p,
  .developer-checklist ul {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .developers-header p,
  .developer-steps article > span,
  .developer-checklist span {
    color: var(--demo-blue);
    font-size: 0.76rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .developers-header h1 {
    color: var(--demo-blue);
    font-family: var(--demo-font-mono);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4.4rem);
    line-height: 0.92;
    max-inline-size: 18ch;
    text-wrap: balance;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .developers-header span {
    max-inline-size: 60rem;
    color: var(--demo-muted);
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.5vw, 1.18rem);
    line-height: 1.55;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }

  .developer-steps {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1px;
    border: 1px solid var(--demo-rule-strong);
    background: var(--demo-rule-strong);
  }

  .developer-steps article,
  .developer-checklist {
    display: grid;
    min-width: 0;
    gap: 0.85rem;
    align-content: start;
    background: var(--demo-paper-wash);
    padding: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.35rem);
  }

  .developer-steps h2,
  .developer-checklist strong {
    color: var(--demo-ink);
    font-size: clamp(1.35rem, 2.4vw, 2rem);
    line-height: 1.08;
    text-wrap: balance;
  }

  .developer-steps p {
    color: var(--demo-muted);
    line-height: 1.45;
  }

  .developer-steps pre {
    overflow: auto;
    margin: 0;
    border: 1px solid rgba(36, 88, 255, 0.34);
    background: #14171f;
    color: #e7ecf4;
    padding: clamp(0.8rem, 2vw, 1rem);
    font-family: var(--demo-font-mono);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  .developer-steps code {
    font: inherit;
  }

  .developer-checklist {
    grid-template-columns: minmax(min(100%, 18rem), 0.35fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
    border: 1px solid var(--demo-rule-strong);
  }

  .developer-checklist strong {
    display: block;
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
  }

  .developer-checklist ul {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.55rem;
    padding-left: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--demo-muted);
    line-height: 1.45;
  }

  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .developers-shell {
      width: min(100% - 1.25rem, 73.75rem);
    }

    .developer-steps,
    .developer-checklist {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .developer-steps pre,
    .developer-steps code {
      white-space: pre-wrap;
      overflow-wrap: anywhere;
    }
  }
</style>
